==Gerald R. Ford Legends Award==
Since 2005, the Rimington Trophy also recognizes legendary centers from the past by presenting the '''President Gerald R. Ford Legendary Center Award''', which is named after [[Gerald Ford]]. The award is presented annually to a former collegiate or professional center who was either a legend on or off the field by making extraordinary contributions through business, civic, or philanthropic endeavors.<ref>{{Cite web|title=GERALD R. FORD LEGENDS AWARD|url=https://www.rimingtontrophy.com/ford/about/|website=rimingtontrophy.com|access-date=March 25, 2024}}</ref>

